			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Vxed! HELP!<a name="60905"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 8 04 1:10 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Did my first Vxed attempt the other nite, since i been more or less away from the game for about 6 months or so, and need to get flagged to join my guild again.
<br />

<br />
So . . . 
<br />

<br />
What exactly am I supposed to be doing in that event?
<br />

<br />
First impression, it seemed as though the enchanter charmed pet was doing between 50 and 75 percent of the total damage output of our group.  Not much need for me to sing any kinda haste or focus effect.
<br />

<br />
Great, so I thought gee these mobs are pretty low resistances, mezz always sticks it seems, maybe I can mezz an add if the chanter is busy, or mezz his pet when charm breaks, etc.  Only problem is that my mezz is about a 4 second cast, if I am really sharp targeting.  I can't count how many times the tank and cleric both died in less than four seconds.  Musta been four or five times at least we had two to four mobs  in camp, all mezzed, and everyone dead but me and the necro.
<br />

<br />
When we got to a named, it was decided to let the chanter pet tank the named, I presume thats the normal procedure?  Anyway the named ate the pet in about 5 seconds or less, then he ate the chanter, then the cleric, etc, etc.
<br />

<br />
I never felt so useless in my life as a bard.  What exactly am I doing in this event, anyway?
<br />

<br />
I mean, I could pull I suppose, but what for?  Even single mobs chewed our a**es.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and mana song?  The way the cleric was chain fast healing the tank on just normal mobs, i doubt very much that mana song made any more difference than haste did.
<br />

<br />
So, what the heck am I supposed to do in this event?</span></td>
