			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vxed! HELP!<a name="60911"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 8 04 2:06 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Get a druid or ranger to put a long lasting snare on the pet before he is charmed.  That way when charm breaks the chanter can run away long enough for you to mez his pet.  He should also tell the group when snare fades so you can stop, break charm, mez, snare and recharm.  As far as what you should be doing --- Pull, pull, Pull.  I go pull as soon as the mob is under control.  Just keep your drum equipped, selo up, hos the next mob, preslow on the way back, mez and snare.  By that time the group should be finished with the last one.  Do your best to single.  A lot of stuff cant be lulled but they all can be mezzed and faded.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
