			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vxed! HELP!<a name="60912"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 8 04 2:06 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I 've done a lot of Vxed trials, and while a charmed pet seems well, all i can say is not to use them for the reason you have experienced. If your groupmates are not geared decently the pet will rip through them as you experienced. I found it best to grab some friends, and hang out in Vxed and kill, take your time, but not too much time. Nameds in Vxed hit for about 1400? its been a while maybe 1600 I know they are hard and Knight Classes *paladins/Shadow Knights* have trouble tanking them if not geared well, and by well I mean Ele plane Knight classes had trouble tanking them when i did the trials.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Pets are too risky, 6 ppl, no enchanter, unless your friend is an enchanter then invite them but you're losing Dps, or you cant find anyone else, you provide haste and mez and mana regen, getting an enchanter in your group is causing a loss of Dps.
<br />

<br />

<br />
your role in Vxed is as it it anywhere else, Haste/Mez/Mana regen/ puller. 
<br />

<br />
Anytime I am in a trial/LDoN or group I'm puller and lead the pace and the success or failure.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Good Luck.</span></td>
