				<td colspan="2"><span>Pulling is a full time job if you're staying at the zone in for the first 30ish kills. Don't pull multiples. Slow on inc. Drop the mob off and go find another, the first will be dead before you get back if there are no mobs in the immediate vicinity. Void tanking works fine on nameds, make sure noone else does anything but send the pet, hit deft and pray the tank is fast when you call it dropping. Nameds will be ~30% when it drops.
<br />

<br />
One tip, keep largos up if you dont trust your snarer. A kyv got away next to the spiritist and ran into the room, it was only half pulled so we had ~five mobs on us. The chanter died quickly. Some roots, lots of mezzes (and quite a few resisted :(), a rez, a dead mob, six tends and clicks later we were flagged and out<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />. Most fun I had had in a long time, but I wouldnt want to repeat it with peoples flags on the line..</span></td>
