			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vxed! HELP!<a name="60949"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 8 04 8:24 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hi there!
<br />

<br />
I play both, bard and chanter (both KT flagged, both got Tipt and Vxed flag in under 5 attempts). I can assure you a SoVed charmed pet is the easiest way and most DPS you can have at a Trial (Tipt or Vxed) by millions of light years.
<br />

<br />
That being said, the chanter has to be not just good, impressive good. I have help flagged a good portion of my guild with my charmed AND SoVed companion, and quite a few times, specially if pick-up groups, they have sent tells during or at end saying they have never seen such pet control, to which I tell them:
<br />

<br />
<i>If the pet controls the master, the master is the pet.</i>
<br />

<br />
Here are some tips about pets and bard role in Trials.
<br />

<br />
MEZZ: chanter mez is 2.5 sec cast. Bard mez is 3.0 cast (as all songs are).
<br />

<br />
While CC might be less of an issue with a chanter in group and the mob being snared, when playing chanter I always welcome a bard mez while recharming. 
<br />

<br />
The reason being, sometimes Cleric just happen to land a biga$$ heal as charm breaks, guess who gets agro? Right. And even though the 1st thing I do is to recast TASH on the loose pet to avoid just that, or to keep agro when snarer lands the snare so that my half channeled Charm doesn&#180;t get OOR should be ex-pet be more interested about snarer, still cleric or nuker or Tank might end up with agro. So bard mez? Sure, I&#180;ll take it any day. Grants me the time I need to wait for snare while retashing and recharming. Specially, if I am the slower and mob is incoming.
<br />

<br />
PET: Have a designated snarer, in my case most times it has been a druid (here is when it comes handy to cast TASH, 1.0 sec cast spell on mob, so snarer is 90% of the times agro free when snare lands and can resume patch healing tank), sometimes has been a ranger.
<br />

<br />
I have a CHARM BROKE key to let snarer know I need snare ASAP, and I tell Snarer to make one to let me know snare landed again and was not resisted, if he doesn&#180;t have it or use it.
<br />

<br />
Place the mob slightly ahead of Tank, and have tank slightly ahead of group, and as chanter, keep enough distance. With charmed and SoVed pet, you kill them so fast, you always have room for recharming. One thing NOT to do is, take forever to pull, I stress the need to pull and make room for my charmed pet. If group wants to go get some named in Vxed that requires staying put at one place because of the lenghty pulls required, I will let the group know bad things will happen due to repops and lack of mobility (being in a corner, nowhere to go, etc). 
<br />

<br />
If after killing something the pet stays put at the point where mob died (instead of going to the designated guard point, as he was supposed to) I will reposition the mob slighty ahead of tank again and lets say, away from cleric?, and while doing so, will try to pass by it as close to wall and far away from it as possible should he break as I am passing him to reposition the mob (this is the only real time of danger for me. If mob is ahead of group, waiting to be pulled, I target that mob, send pet to it, pet moves forward. When at desired spot, I tell it to come back, and right away to guard. This avoids passing by pet if I don&#180;t have to).
<br />

<br />
Pet number 1 cause of wipes? Only if chanter sucks, and yes, I have died to pet on occasions. Everytime I had pet we made it to the Tipt named though, some we won, some we lost. I also remind the group periodically that should I die, to please ROOT pet (bard mez would be welcomed here as well).
<br />

<br />
I have had a 5 ghost pull (pathing is horrible, one will come forward, and there you have it, a 5 pull) tanked-mezzed by pet alone. All agroed pet, while giving me enough time to mez them one by one, ghosts are pretty gimp hitters, when compared to what is around.
<br />

<br />
Pally in group stunning pet helps with pet control? Sure do, but if they ask me at the beginning of the trail what do I need for pet control I always say, SNARE ASAP. And if bard in group, assisting with mez on loose pet will not hurt any either.
<br />

<br />
NAMEDs: Sending pet to tank named only works with Momma Cragbeast. Vxed Pooka named will indded tear the pet away, Tipt final boss kills pet in 3 or 4 secs.
<br />

<br />
Yes, sometimes there is a red con named popping at the right side camp in final room with flagging NPC.
<br />

<br />
Having a ranger in group pretty much guaranties Tipt final boss kill. Have ranger pull named and hit WS. Ranger has to be away from camp a bit so that AE rampage doesn&#180;t hit healers.  Send pet. Now the tricky part, NO ONE cast anything on named or ranger, as in NOBODY. No heals, no slow, no nothing. WS offed, bye ranja. Now mob is on pet, mob still needs NO spells (slow) casted on him. Pet has been previously buffed with Virtue. Healers start spamming heals on pet. Bye named. Gratz.
<br />

<br />
BARD ROLE: If anyone still things pet is a waste of DPS and you better off not invitnig a chanter over for flag. Think again. NOTHING pulls faster than a bard, and charm clock is ticking, so chain pull to pet and tank (without killing them), no reason to have pet sitting for 20 secs, pet can kill a mob in around 10 secs. When my slow gets resisted (chanter slow is 6.0 cast, mine is lat ike 5.1 or something like that) sometimes I do not have time for the second slow to land! Thus, as someone said, PULL PULL PULL, and assist with mezzes on loose pets.
<br />

<br />
I have no preferences on pets, I pet the first Hynid, Pooka or Cragbeast that comes along (I don&#180;t give them mage weapons, stuns are bad).
<br />

<br />
Necro? Yes, necro is nice for FD-rez recovery. Summon Corpse? Sure, but if no necro bard can ninja drag the corpses to zone (you can drag 2 corpses at a time using /corpsedrag).
<br />

<br />
Overall, I like Tipt or Vxed trials because I enjoy charming, and its about the only place where charm is allowed in GoD.
<br />

<br />
EDIT: When no snarer in group I still get charmed pet, since snarer place is most likely being taken by shamman, I just don&#180;t haste it, and I have to be twice as far from pet. I will mez it while he is coming at me, Tash it again, nuke mob a few times, and before mez fades, recharm pet (again, bard mez would safe a h*ll of a lot of time wasted with pet doing nothing, cause even if I mez pet first, as I should, I will still ask for SNARE - granted, bard snare - and after mob is bard snared, nuke mez off, recharm, and there you go, pet back at mob in no time. Sure beats waiting for 1 min and about 15 secs for mez to break anyday).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
