				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vxed! HELP!<a name="60981"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 8 04 10:37 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Good adivice above about the pet management.
<br />

<br />
I kinda disagree that you have to be a stellar enchanter to pull it off (not saying you're NOT stellar, but I've managed it and gotten compliments while playing my hubby's chanter, and it was about the second time I've ever played a chanter other than to buff).
<br />

<br />
I would say that the biggest things with using a chanter pet are 1. chanter must stay alert and not have RL stuff going on, seems simple enough; 2. chanter must park pet at the front of camp and then stay far away from the pet; 3. people must understand the rule of 3 if the pet is tanking (pet will hold agro if three or fewer PC's are on the agro list, if a 4th gets on agro mob will ignore pet).
<br />

<br />
I've done both Vxed and Tipt with and without chanter pets -- as my paladin, who is EP and a few Time pieces (we are newish to Time still).  With a sharp healer and a back up healer I can tank the stuff, but it's no picnic.  When we have a pet we usually have me tank anyway and just use the pet for DPS and to tank if I need a break or am dead - that way mobs die so fast, I dont have time to die usually.
<br />

<br />
Bards are great for a few reasons but one important one is that the bard mez lasts 18 seconds, that is enough time (if folks are paying attention) to re-tash, re-snare, re-Malos the pet and re-charm, and then your charmed pet isn't standing around mezed for a while.
<br />

<br />
A tip I found in Vxed  or Tipt as a paladin: all mobs that are charmable, are stunnable. I keep my longest lasting stun memmed and I keep the chanter pet as my second (toggle last two targets) target, and if the chanter yells or I see the pet's agro message I toggle and stun it, that gives up to 10 seconds of the pet standing around, and with luck I can do this even while in combat with the current target. You might could use the Brusco's song for this, I haven't played with it much since I got it on my bard (who is now 61). 
<br />

<br />
If you have a spare paladin (two tanks actually work out pretty well here), they can babysit the pet (being ready to stun, healing the chanter, etc) and make things a lot easier.  I actually do the same when I'm playing my cleric in the trials (Tarnation lands); I always clear it with the chanter firt of course.  
<br />

<br />
One of the smoothest Tipt runs I ever had was with Warrior, Paladin, Cleric, Necro, Ranger and Shaman. The warrior (who is equivalently geared to my pally) could tank though it was still a challenge. Without pet breaks we made good progress -  even though the mobs took longer to die, they really don't have THAT many hp - and the Ranger Weaponshielded the named at the end, then we just burned him down.  
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
