		</table></td><td class="PanelBodyAlternate" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vxed! HELP!<a name="61084"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 8 04 11:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If all you want is to win and you don't care about nameds/augs or anything here's a great way to contribute as a bard... and it's hella fun too. 
<br />

<br />
Stay at zone for the entire time, pull until the Stonespiritist pops. Mem DA and wait till it pops. Get HP buffs up, lev the group, invis the group via a caster class (helps to delay aggro), fire up selo's and start running. Run along the walls, don't get stuck, and don't stop. When you get to the 2nd to last dog before the last room slow down a split second, warn your group (you should've been auto'running the entire time and just using left/right to change direction), and hit DA. The DA enables the people who need the flag to stop and either hit the hotkey they've prepared or say the key word (all they have to say is &quot;tend&quot; ) and the rest of you to click out in a timely fashion. Hopefully they've all been hit at least once on the way up so their invis has dropped automatically... but if they haven't make sure they all realize they have to take it off before the Stonespiritist will give the flag.
<br />

<br />
As the bard, don't be afraid to fade every so often because you are the only one that HAS to be alive at the top to DA the group and give them a chance to live.
<br />

<br />
You don't have to be only EP or better, although that's who I've done it with mostly. If you wanted it to work with worse gear the easiest way would be to send the already vxed flagged people first, then the bard (you need to live to group DA) and the people who need the flag last, which is how we did it when we wiped at the top and said &quot;F*** it&quot; and just ran. Basically the more unimportant people get initial aggro and so have a better chance of getting smacked, stunned, and run over leaving the people behind them to run on and leave the first people (and their mobs, briefly) behind.
<br />

<br />
It can be suicidal if you're not on your toes though. 
<br />

<br />
Pros: -you don't need an enchanter or shaman, the bard can single pull everything to entrance and slow
<br />
-can be done if you've wiped countless times and people are ready to give up
<br />
-can stack the group with non-flagged right before you kill the last mob before the spawn (the hynids at the entrance ARE kiteable bye a group of pure casters, for example)
<br />

<br />
Cons: -it's not the right way to do it
<br />
-it's dangerous and the possibility of people dying is probably significant, especially if you don't usually do stuff like that
<br />
-unless you have a bard in group this won't work, there isn't time for a DA class to stop and cast self DA so it has to be done on the run and you HAVE to have selo's to do this, soe/sow/billy just aren't fast enough
<br />

<br />
Anyway, just my 2 cents... but I live for the adrenaline rush lately *lol* Have fun!!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Muse Flayre N'Grayce < House Archon >
Don't run baby, you'll just die tired ~.-</span></td>
