				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vxed! HELP!<a name="61112"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 9 04 5:08 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Most of my successful Vxed / Tipt runs are withOUT enchanter charming pets. I have to admit that when everything goes smooth, enchanter charmed pet makes those trials much faster. However, unless I know the enchanter can handle charming, i would perfer to go petless.
<br />

<br />
As for our roles, as usual, chain pull mobs to group one at a time. I always try to slow the mob on the pull. Even if there is enchanter in group, I still mez adds until enchanter's mez lands. If group is using charmed pet, I make sure I have the pet on my target buffer and mez pet on charm breaks. If no charmed pet, I make sure group is moving at a decent pace and stay ahead of respawn. (if the group can't stay ahead of respawn, this group is very unlikely to be able to pass the trials)
<br />

<br />
For Vxed, usually my group kill about 30 mobs at the zone in, then start plowing up. Usually by the time we are about to reach the NPC room, the NPC would spawn. This saves time, and much safer than the DA run method. I have bad experience with DA run method. 2 out of 3 times I've tried it, somebody died during the run, and they were the ones who actually needed the flags <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-13.gif" border="0" alt="LOL" hspace="2" /> .</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
