				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vxed! HELP!<a name="61203"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 9 04 4:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Any number of people could/should be helping the chanter control their pet if possible.
<br />

<br />
If you're not out pulling when their charm breaks, MEZ the pet.
<br />

<br />
If you are the cleric, and you see charm break, STUN the pet.
<br />

<br />
If you can cast root, and you see charm break, ROOT the pet.
<br />

<br />
If you are the chanter, always ask for a snare on the pet... and if snare wears off before charm does, BREAK charm and get it re-snared.
<br />

<br />
If you make management a group effort you retain insane DPS with much lower risk.
<br />

<br />

<br />
As for a bard's role in vxed.. there is no reason to pull multiples in vxed, and if your group can't handle a single pre-slowed mob, you should seek your flag elsewhere, or wait until they can.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
